
## Implementation

- Files: `src/update_tool.ml` (new), `src/tool_registry.ml`, channel handlers, `src/dune`
- find_repo_root: walk up from Sys.executable_name looking for dune-project or .git
- run_update ~send_progress:
  1. git -C root pull via Lwt_process — non-fatal on non-zero, stream output
  2. make -C root build via Lwt_process.pread_lines — fatal on non-zero (do NOT restart)
  3. On success: send "Build complete. Restarting..." then Unix.kill (Unix.getpid ()) Sys.sigusr1
- Guard: if !draining then return "Restart already in progress"
- Register as tool "update_clawq" in tool_registry.ml
- Add /update pre-dispatch check in channel message handlers (before routing to agent)
- See `.plan/2026-03-06-amber-circuit/update-command.md`

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] /update in any channel triggers git pull + make build + restart
- [ ] git pull failure is reported but does not abort build
- [ ] make build failure aborts with error message, does NOT restart
- [ ] Agent can call update_clawq tool to self-update
- [ ] Output streamed progressively (not buffered until end)
- [ ] Guard: /update while draining returns immediate error
- [ ] find_repo_root returns None gracefully when not in a repo
